Sentencas: The performance degradation of a solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) single cell caused by delamination of the cathode is investigated.
Titulo: Fast performance degradation of SOFC caused by cathode delamination in long-term testing

Sentencas: When the TEC difference between the cathode and the electrolyte is large, detachment of the interface occurs.
Titulo: Fast performance degradation of SOFC caused by cathode delamination in long-term testing

Sentencas: This is confirmed by SEM images and impedance analysis during long-term operation.
Titulo: Fast performance degradation of SOFC caused by cathode delamination in long-term testing

Sentencas: As delamination occurs, the active area naturally decreases, and the oxygen reduction reaction concentrates into the intact area.
Titulo: Fast performance degradation of SOFC caused by cathode delamination in long-term testing

Sentencas: This leads to an increase in polarization and ohmic losses so that the performance of the single cell degrades by approximately 7.7% during 1000 h of operation.
Titulo: Fast performance degradation of SOFC caused by cathode delamination in long-term testing

Sentencas: Assuming that the drop of power density was due only to delamination, the area change is approximately 10% when the TEC difference is 7 x 10(-6) K(-1).
Titulo: Fast performance degradation of SOFC caused by cathode delamination in long-term testing
